---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="AI Leadership Templates | AILD.org"
  description="Practical templates for executive decision briefs, trust controls, workflow cadence, and AI outcome dashboards."
  canonical="https://aild.org/templates/"
  active="templates"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Leadership toolkit</p>
    <h1>Templates that convert AI into decision quality and execution speed.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Recommended order: <a href="/learn/ai-decision-intelligence-stack-executives/">Decision framework</a> ->
      <a href="/learn/trust-vs-override-framework/">Trust/override rules</a> ->
      <a href="/learn/ai-augmented-executive-workflow/">Executive workflow</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Template 01: Executive Decision Brief</h3>
      <p>Decision question, options, assumptions, risk, owner, and deadline.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Template 02: Trust vs Override Log</h3>
      <p>AI recommendation, human override reason, final decision, and review date.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Template 03: Weekly Executive Workflow Board</h3>
      <p>Signal brief, priority decisions, action owners, and Friday calibration.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Template 04: AI Leadership KPI Dashboard</h3>
      <p>Decision cycle time, quality score, execution completion, and rework rate.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section panel">
    <h2>Where to apply these templates</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Monthly strategic planning and portfolio prioritization</li>
      <li>Cross-functional operating reviews with conflicting constraints</li>
      <li>Risk-sensitive approvals requiring human accountability</li>
      <li>Weekly leadership meetings that need faster action conversion</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
